    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ h(t) = {\frac{t^{4}-10t^{3}+25t^{2}}{5t^{4}-23t^{3}-10t^{2}}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>h(t)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{t-5}{5t+2}, t\ne 5\hbox{ and }t\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   h(t) \amp = {\frac{t^{4}-10t^{3}+25t^{2}}{5t^{4}-23t^{3}-10t^{2}}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(t^{2}-10t+25\right)}}{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(5t^{2}-23t-10\right)}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(t-5\right)^{2}}}{{t^{2}\mathopen{}\left(5t+2\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-5\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{t-5}{5t+2}, t\ne 5\hbox{ and }t\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since <m>t^{2}(t - 5)</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>t \ne {5, 0}</m>.</p>
</solution>
